				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The Super NES's RAM at $7E0000-$7FFFFF is DRAM. DRAM doesn't <em>guarantee</em> remanence past a couple frames, which is why the S-CPU takes a few cycles out of the middle of each scanline to refresh memory. But the value can persist for several seconds, longer if cooler. See <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cold_boot_attack" class="postlink">cold boot attack</a>.<br /><br />Can anyone with a logic analyzer look at the reset and ROM enable lines during power loss to see what happens?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

